Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Casa Grande, Cerro Verde, Pomalca

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-05-25T21:28:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/peru-stocks-buenaventura-casa-grande-cerro-verde-pomalca.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index gained 1 percent to 21,999.71. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 1.1 percent to 2,832.64.  Copper and gold miners gained after metals advanced in New
York, said Ernesto Ferrand, a trader at Lima-based brokerage
Andes Securities SAB.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration
company, jumped 9.4 percent to $2.55 after GMP Securities
analyst George Albino rated the stock a new “buy.” Sociedad
Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan
Copper & Gold Inc., rose 4.2 percent to $42.20.  Candente Copper
Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, gained 3 percent
to $1.73. Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, advanced for an eighth day,
adding 1.9 percent to $42.50.  Sugar producers rose after prices climbed for a second day
in New York.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a unit of
Grupo Oviedo, gained 1.9 percent to 55 centimos.  Casa Grande 
(CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer and a unit of
Gloria SA, rose 1.6 percent to 15.95 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  